{"id":"memory-event:1774734719845440000","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:74","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:74","anchors":[{"Lineage":"lineage:1683"},{"Lineage":"lineage:2211"},{"Lineage":"lineage:3566"},{"Lineage":"lineage:6426"},{"Lineage":"lineage:877"},{"Lineage":"lineage:951"},{"Lineage":"lineage:9774"},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_agent","path":"prism_agent","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_cli","path":"prism_cli::main","kind":"Function"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_core","path":"prism_core::validation_feedback","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_ir","path":"prism_ir","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::compact_tools","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::dashboard_router","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_store","path":"prism_store","kind":"Module"}}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"The repo-wide architecture hierarchy is now materially balanced at the top level: every direct child of `concept://prism_architecture` has at least one internal child concept, and most major subsystems now split into reusable module-level packets. Important newer boundaries are the IR trio (`concept://graph_identity_and_parse_ir`, `concept://anchor_change_and_lineage_ir`, `concept://plan_and_coordination_ir`), the persistence trio (`concept://sqlite_and_graph_persistence`, `concept://memory_projection_persistence`, `concept://history_snapshot_and_resolution`), the compact-tool pair (`concept://compact_discovery_and_opening`, `concept://compact_expansion_and_concept_views`), the CLI pair, the dashboard pair, the validation pair, and the inference branch `concept://inferred_edge_runtime_and_session_store`. Future sessions should traverse these concept packets before reopening crate facades.","metadata":{"evidence":{"coChangeLineages":[],"eventIds":[],"memoryIds":[],"validationChecks":[]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774734719,"publishedAt":1774734719,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85"},"created_at":1774734719,"source":"Agent","trust":0.92},"recordedAt":1774734719,"taskId":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:1774735144889720000","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:75","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:75","anchors":[{"Lineage":"lineage:10673"},{"Lineage":"lineage:10790"},{"Lineage":"lineage:12779"},{"Lineage":"lineage:3460"},{"Lineage":"lineage:4145"},{"Lineage":"lineage:5310"},{"Lineage":"lineage:6149"},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_core","path":"prism_core::concept_events","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::daemon_mode","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::query_runtime","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::tool_args","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_projections","path":"prism_projections::concepts","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_query","path":"prism_query::plan_completion","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_query","path":"prism_query::symbol","kind":"Module"}}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"The architecture map now has a third layer inside the densest branches. `semantic_projection_indexes` splits into packet materialization (`concept://concept_relation_and_intent_projections`) and derived co-change/validation indexes (`concept://cochange_and_validation_projection_indexes`); the query layer splits symbol/source, impact/outcome, coordination/runtime, and plan-insight reads; the MCP runtime splits query execution, resource serving, mutation/schema contracts, session-state mutation runtime, daemon/process lifecycle, and server-health views; and the concept-publication pipeline now exposes explicit concept/relation event streams plus published-knowledge/memory logs. Future architecture reasoning should descend through those child concepts before reopening crate facades.","metadata":{"evidence":{"coChangeLineages":[],"eventIds":[],"memoryIds":[],"validationChecks":[]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774735144,"publishedAt":1774735144,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85"},"created_at":1774735144,"source":"Agent","trust":0.92},"recordedAt":1774735144,"taskId":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:1774735787389338000","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:78","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:78","anchors":[{"Lineage":"lineage:1139"},{"Lineage":"lineage:1596"},{"Lineage":"lineage:5681"},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_coordination","path":"prism_coordination::state","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_core","path":"prism_core::session","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_memory","path":"prism_memory::session","kind":"Module"}}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"Architecture split refined and verified: prism-memory now has durable child branches for recall/scoring, outcome-and-session history, and semantic/structural models; prism-core splits workspace refresh into core indexing versus workspace session runtime; prism-coordination splits into state model versus operations/policy, each with two internal child concepts. Later broad reasoning about memory, workspace refresh, or coordination should start from these concept branches instead of reopening crate roots.","metadata":{"evidence":{"coChangeLineages":[],"eventIds":[],"memoryIds":[],"validationChecks":[]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774735787,"publishedAt":1774735787,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85"},"created_at":1774735787,"source":"Agent","trust":0.9},"recordedAt":1774735787,"taskId":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:1774736197305668000","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:81","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:81","anchors":[{"Lineage":"lineage:1818"},{"Lineage":"lineage:5873"},{"Lineage":"lineage:9774"},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_curator","path":"prism_curator","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::compact_tools","kind":"Module"}},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_parser","path":"prism_parser","kind":"Module"}}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"Architecture hierarchy deepened in three broad areas. The adapter stack now has a shared parser-contract layer plus concrete Rust, Python, Markdown, and structured-config sub-pipelines. The curator flow now splits into backend execution/prompting versus rule synthesis/proposal typing. The compact tool surface now splits into locate/text-candidate ranking, open/workset follow-through, concept/expand decode, and task-brief coordination summaries. Future architecture reasoning should traverse those concepts before reopening the adapter, curator, or compact-tool code directly.","metadata":{"evidence":{"coChangeLineages":[],"eventIds":[],"memoryIds":[],"validationChecks":[]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774736197,"publishedAt":1774736197,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85"},"created_at":1774736197,"source":"Agent","trust":0.92},"recordedAt":1774736197,"taskId":"task:map-the-full-prism-architecture-into-durable-repo-concepts-and-concept-relations-for-future-agent-reasoning:85","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:01kmwfk9m5pgpa4sf6hm8mnfdw","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:01kmwfk9m5skznfys67588df6j","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:01kmwfk9m5skznfys67588df6j","anchors":[{"Lineage":"lineage:16166"},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_ir","path":"prism_ir::durable_ids::new_prefixed_id","kind":"Function"}}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"Repo-persisted Prism entities that can be created by independent runtimes must use globally unique sortable IDs instead of process-local counters or raw timestamps. Semantic NodeIds stay path-based and session handles stay runtime-local; durable shared identities such as memories, plans, coordination tasks, claims, artifacts, reviews, lineage records, curator jobs, inferred edges, observed events, sessions, and emitted outcome or memory events should use the shared sortable ID helper.","metadata":{"evidence":{"coChangeLineages":[],"eventIds":[],"memoryIds":[],"validationChecks":[]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774777378,"publishedAt":1774777378,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:replace-merge-unsafe-counter-based-repo-ids-with-globally-unique-timestamp-ordered-ids-across-memory-and-coordination-persistence:135"},"created_at":1774777378,"source":"Agent","trust":0.93},"recordedAt":1774777378,"taskId":"task:replace-merge-unsafe-counter-based-repo-ids-with-globally-unique-timestamp-ordered-ids-across-memory-and-coordination-persistence:135","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:01kmwpc4w33tjveeqr3q1sbp84","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:01kmwpc4w3rp0pfy6pce3w3816","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:01kmwpc4w3rp0pfy6pce3w3816","anchors":[{"Lineage":"lineage:01kmwnhy16pe16x0d5w32x0nsm"},{"Node":{"crate_name":"prism_mcp","path":"prism_mcp::tests_support::temp_workspace","kind":"Function"}}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"Parallel prism-mcp tests should not derive temporary workspace directories from wall-clock timestamps alone. A live refactor run surfaced SQLite `database is locked` failures when extracted test modules ran concurrently; switching `temp_workspace` to `new_sortable_token()` removes the naming-collision path and makes the shared test harness safer under parallel execution.","metadata":{"evidence":{"coChangeLineages":[],"eventIds":[],"memoryIds":[],"validationChecks":[]},"files":["crates/prism-mcp/src/tests_support.rs","crates/prism-mcp/src/tests/query_history.rs"],"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774784484,"publishedAt":1774784484,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:create-a-prism-coordination-plan-for-refactoring-the-prism-mcp-test-suite-to-reduce-slowness-and-flakiness:01kmwmw41s7vz3y8wmfgnfh0hm"},"created_at":1774784484,"source":"Agent","trust":0.88},"recordedAt":1774784484,"taskId":"task:create-a-prism-coordination-plan-for-refactoring-the-prism-mcp-test-suite-to-reduce-slowness-and-flakiness:01kmwmw41s7vz3y8wmfgnfh0hm","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:01kn07e726z4zb1j640w19dx9b","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:01kn07e726myjcgr1rsj33nf6j","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:01kn07e726myjcgr1rsj33nf6j","anchors":[{"File":104},{"File":231},{"File":260},{"File":317}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"PRISM daemon health depends on keeping authoritative runtime state, bounded serving projections, and cold analytical evidence separate. Symbol-level co-change is analytical evidence, not hot runtime history: persisting unbounded pairwise co-change or hydrating it into HistoryStore makes cache growth, startup memory, and refresh lock contention explode. Co-change should stay bounded in serving projections, while any colder evidence must remain off the daemon hot path.","metadata":{"evidence":{"validationChecks":["cargo test -p prism-history -p prism-projections -p prism-store","cargo build --release -p prism-cli -p prism-mcp"]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774903041,"publishedAt":1774903041,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:promote-strongest-recent-session-memories-into-repo-scoped-memory:01kn07dmzs2qw5q5d2q2a6pgsv"},"created_at":1774903041,"source":"Agent","trust":0.95},"recordedAt":1774903041,"taskId":"task:promote-strongest-recent-session-memories-into-repo-scoped-memory:01kn07dmzs2qw5q5d2q2a6pgsv","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:01kn07e79g04xxxwr9c11mramm","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:01kn07e79gh5je3z1zk8zgg3qf","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:01kn07e79gh5je3z1zk8zgg3qf","anchors":[{"File":164},{"File":187},{"File":241}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"Native plan-node completion must honor successful validation outcomes correlated directly to the node id, because MCP commonly uses a native node id as the current task while recording `test_ran` and `fix_validated` events with no anchors. If completion logic only accepts anchor-matched evidence or real coordination-task ids, `plan_node_update` can reject completion even after the exact required validations were run and recorded.","metadata":{"evidence":{"validationChecks":["cargo test -p prism-query native_plan_node_completion_accepts_task_correlated_validations_without_anchors -- --nocapture","cargo test -p prism-mcp native_plan_node_completion_accepts_current_task_validation_events_without_anchors -- --nocapture"]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774903041,"publishedAt":1774903041,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:promote-strongest-recent-session-memories-into-repo-scoped-memory:01kn07dmzs2qw5q5d2q2a6pgsv"},"created_at":1774903041,"source":"Agent","trust":0.93},"recordedAt":1774903041,"taskId":"task:promote-strongest-recent-session-memories-into-repo-scoped-memory:01kn07dmzs2qw5q5d2q2a6pgsv","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
{"id":"memory-event:01kn07e7gt5061cfzeagyks7gd","action":"stored","memoryId":"memory:01kn07e7gtqccwq2yj9fhy2r1k","scope":"repo","entry":{"id":"memory:01kn07e7gtqccwq2yj9fhy2r1k","anchors":[{"File":260},{"File":72},{"File":75},{"File":81}],"kind":"Episodic","scope":"repo","content":"After the co-change rewrite, the next major daemon-memory risks are eager curator hydration and oversized PatchApplied outcomes, with full history-event hydration still contributing. The live cache showed a single curator snapshot row of about 29 MB JSON that is always loaded into CuratorHandle state, and PatchApplied events dominated outcome_event_log because they embed large `metadata.changedSymbols` arrays. Future daemon-memory work should target those surfaces before chasing SQLite mapping effects.","metadata":{"evidence":{"validationChecks":["./target/release/prism-cli mcp status","./target/release/prism-cli mcp health"]},"provenance":{"kind":"manual_memory","origin":"manual_store"},"publication":{"lastReviewedAt":1774903041,"publishedAt":1774903041,"status":"active"},"task_id":"task:promote-strongest-recent-session-memories-into-repo-scoped-memory:01kn07dmzs2qw5q5d2q2a6pgsv"},"created_at":1774903041,"source":"Agent","trust":0.9},"recordedAt":1774903041,"taskId":"task:promote-strongest-recent-session-memories-into-repo-scoped-memory:01kn07dmzs2qw5q5d2q2a6pgsv","promotedFrom":[],"supersedes":[]}
